t apply to wide-band data\nsets. The standard method for estimating the measurement uncertainty in RM is\nnot accurate for sources with non-zero spectral indices. Furthermore, dividing\nStokes Q and U by Stokes I to correct for spectral index effects, in\ncombination with RM synthesis, does not maximize the likelihood.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2016 21:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Oct 2017 18:00:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-25"}
