cular weight and temperature gradients, and that low-Z models\nlead to a much more general disagreement with solar data. We also show that,\nwhile simple parametrizations of opacity uncertainties can strongly alleviate\nthe solar abundance problem, they are insufficient to substantially improve the\nagreement of SSMs with helioseismic data beyond that obtained for high-Z models\ndue to the intrinsic correlations of theoretical predictions. All the detailed\ninformation of the new solar models, can be found online:\nhttp://www.ice.cat/personal/aldos/Solar_Data.html\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Nov 2016 21:00:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Dec 2016 10:12:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 28 Dec 2016 08:20:36 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 13 Feb 2017 11:56:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-14"}
